widgets_values:
#  VRGDG HUMO Music Video Workflow

This workflow creates **music videos (or other videos)** in **one shot** using the **HUMO model**.  

---

A medium shot of a man with dark brown wavy hair walking through a chamber littered with broken stone statues. The camera tracks in a slow orbit around him as his boots crunch over shards, his leather jacket catching faint glimmers of moonlight through the fractured ceiling above

A chest-up shot as a man kneels in front of a cracked wall, pressing his palm against it. Ember light seeps faintly through the cracks, glowing across his shoulder tattoo. The camera tilts downward from above, framing him in isolation, his breath visible in the cold air

A tracking shot from ground level as a man with layered dark brown hair drags a heavy chain behind him across a stone floor. The camera follows its metallic scrape, then rises to reveal his stern silhouette lit by flickering torches mounted on the walls

A medium shot of a woman spinning slowly in a sunlit bedroom, the grain heavy, air thick with summer warmth. Her bare shoulders glisten with sweat as she moves in rhythm to unseen music, static blooming on her skin as she turns toward the lens.

A medium profile shot of a man walking past a row of extinguished candles. He reaches out, brushing one with his hand, and a faint flame sparks to life. The camera pans around his face as the glow illuminates his eyes, shifting the ambience from cold blue to dim orange

A handheld close-up of a woman inserting a cassette tape into a dusty player. The sunlight leaks through blinds, flaring across the lens. As she presses play, the tape spins, reflections shimmer in her eyes, the analog imperfections glowing warmly.

An over-the-shoulder shot of a man standing at the entrance of a firelit ruin, his outline stark against the red-orange glow. The camera slowly pushes forward beside him, capturing both his profile and the looming skeletal arches that tower ahead, embers drifting across the frame

A wide shot of a living room floor covered in tangled cords and photos. A woman sits barefoot on the carpet, backlit by a window, surrounded by scattered memories. The 90s camcorder grain softens every edge into a tender, faded hue.

A wide sweeping crane shot of a man with medium-length dark brown hair standing at the center of a circular stone chamber, arms slightly spread. Candles line the perimeter, their flames trembling as if reacting to his presence. The camera arcs overhead, the scene bathed in haunting shafts of moonlight and rising smoke

A slow zoom toward a woman framed by flickering sunlight, sitting cross-legged by an old tape recorder. Dust catches in the beam of light. Every frame of her movement feels remembered, soaked in soft blur and vintage golden tone.

A close-up of a womans reflection in a mirror clouded with age. She moves slightly, the image doubling and ghosting like a tape glitch. The warm grain softens every detail as if each flicker itself remembers her.

A handheld close-up of a womans hands hovering above a stack of photographs. The sunlight flickers through blinds, casting stripes across her arms as she pauses, holding the moment still in the warm analog haze of early 90s film.

A slow dolly shot of a woman standing in the doorway, the curtains moving with a faint breeze. The color fades toward sepia as she exhales and lets the light rest on her face, holding still as if to let it stay forever.

A slow dolly-in to a woman in a white tank and shorts standing in a faded kitchen. Dust motes swirl around her as she stares into empty space, almost sensing someone beside her. The handheld camera trembles softly under nostalgic golden light.

A close-up of a mans hand, rough and scarred, gripping a rusted chain that dangles from the ceiling. The camera pans upward along his arm, revealing ritual tattoos illuminated by cold blue shafts of light, before tilting to catch his expressioneyes distant, jaw tense, as if listening to unseen voices

nodes.title: Start
widgets_values:
## Set Video Resolution 
- Define the **Width** and **Height** for the final video.  
- Keep values **divisible by 16** for best results.  
- Larger sizes = better quality but longer render times.  

## KEEP THIS SET TO FIXED

widgets_values:

- **Do not remove or change this node.**  
- Doing so will **cause the workflow to break**.

A wide shot of a woman walking through a sunlit corridor. The slow handheld camera follows her steps as golden hour light glows on her shoulders. The scene feels slow, like time stretched, capturing her in nostalgic afterglow.

A medium close-up of a woman sitting near a half-open window, light flaring on the lens. Her fingers trace the windowpane as if capturing a memory suspended in dust, the afterglow of day melting into the analog warmth of the shot.

A medium shot tracking behind a man with layered dark brown wavy hair as he moves down a cracked stone corridor. His tribal tattoo glints faintly under torchlight, his hand brushing along walls etched with faint occult markings. The camera follows close, panning across glowing cracks in the stone that pulse with ember light

A low angle shot of a woman in a loose shirt and denim shorts walking barefoot through a cluttered living room, muted sunlight leaking through blinds. The handheld camera drifts slightly as she passes an old TV playing an old parade, color bleeding with analog imperfection.

A medium shot of a woman sitting on a bed in soft dusk light. The air glows with muted amber as she runs her hand over a pillows edge. The handheld camera tilts slightly, catching the way the light fades away across her face.

nodes.title: Canceling a run?
widgets_values:
>  **Important Reminder**  
> If you cancel a run but it keeps Q'uing runs:

nodes.title: Start
widgets_values:
## Audio Scale 
- This setting works well but if the mouth moves to much or to big drop this to 1.00 or if the mouth does not move enough you can raise this value

nodes.title: Step 2
widgets_values:
##  Step 2: Choose Audio File 
- Load your **audio file** into the workflow.  
- The lyrics will be separated out.  
- The audio will be split into **per-scene snippets** for video generation.  
- If you are already using a stem that contains only the lyrics, you can **bypass the Mel-Band RoFormer nodes**.

nodes.title: Mel-Band RoFormer Nodes
widgets_values:
##  Important: Audio Separation Node

- **Do not remove or change this node** unless you are intentionally bypassing it.  
- This node extracts the **vocals** from the main audio.  
- You may bypass this node **only if** you are using a **vocals-only audio file** in the first Audio Load node in step 2.

nodes.title: Step 3
widgets_values:
##  Step 3: Enter Folder Name 


- Enter the **folder name** where your video output files will be stored.
- The folder will be automatically created inside your **comfyui/output** folder.
- Make sure the folder is **empty** before you begin.
- This will be used for the videos that will later be combined into one.
- I normally just put the name of the song, and a folder with that name will be created automatically. See left note for more details.
## Do not put a file path! Just a folder name
- If you forget to change this and your doing a new run it will create a new folder with the same name but add V2 at the end.

nodes.title: Audio Crop Node
widgets_values:
##  Important: Audio Setup
- Here we get the audio from the **first Audio Load** node.  
- If you are **not using the Vocal Separator** and are working with a song that already has vocals removed, you must load the **full version** of the song here.  
  - Otherwise, the final video will only include the isolated vocals.  

### Simplified Setup
- A second **Load Audio** node has already been added and bypassed for you.  
- To use it:  
  1. Change the **get_audioFile** node to **AudioFile2**.  
  2. Un-bypass the second **Load Audio** node.  
  3. Load the **full audio with instruments** into it.  

Thats it  the workflow will automatically route everything correctly so the **final video** has the full track.

nodes.title: NOTE
widgets_values:
##  Important NOTE
- The reason the **LLM string is connected to the neg prompt** in the first text encoder is to control workflow timing.  
- If this connection is removed, the workflow will run too quickly and the LLM will not have enough time to send prompts. As a result, some groups will not receive prompts.  
- This connection **must remain in place**.  
- Negative prompts are not used in this workflow, since **CFG must be 1 when using LightX** so this won't effect anything.  

- This is also why we have filename on each video combine node connected to the neg prompt on the next neg prompt. Same thing. Keep things in order.

nodes.title: step 1
widgets_values:
##  Step 1: Upload Reference Image 
- Use **Load Image** to set your main reference.  
- There is a **Background Removal** node to remove the background.  
- Use the **Resize Image v2** node to adjust dimensions. Choose **Crop** if the image already matches the video aspect ratio; if not, switch to **Pad** to fit without cutting important parts.

A medium shot inside a narrow hallway lined with peeling wallpaper. Dust drifts through the amber light as a woman in a worn slip leans against the wall, her gaze lost in thought like a memory caught on the edges of a fading home video.

A wide low-angle shot inside a ruined cathedral, shafts of moonlight piercing through shattered stained glass. A man with medium-length dark brown wavy hair steps slowly into the frame, his black leather attire catching faint blue glows as drifting ash swirls around him. The camera cranes upward, revealing chains swinging gently overhead

##  Important: Prompt Splitter Node

---

##  GPT Workflow Overview

### 1 [Wan Humo Lyric Segment Typo Fixer](https://chatgpt.com/g/g-68f54394667c8191ac2dc05f1af0a458-wan-humo-lyric-segment-typo-fixer)
- This GPT takes the **lyric segment** and the **main lyrics** as input.  
- It **fixes typos**, improves readability, and ensures proper structure and phrasing.  
- The goal is to make sure each lyric segment is clean and ready for prompt generation.  
-  **Output:** Corrected and polished lyric segments.  

---

### 2 [Wan Humo Music Video Prompt Creator](https://chatgpt.com/g/g-68d0a5a9f7b4819189bdb15c826c789c-wanhumo-music-video-prompt-creator)
- This GPT takes the **corrected lyric segments** and the **story or visual concept**.  
- It generates a **JSON string** of cinematic text-to-video prompts.  
- Each prompt includes **camera motion, lighting, and visual storytelling** elements.  
-  **Output:** A detailed JSON set of prompts ready for verification or rendering.  

---

### 3 [Story to Lyric Verification GPT (Optional)](https://chatgpt.com/g/g-68cdd761c9308191a727a851443596a6-story-to-lyric-verification)
- This GPT checks alignment between the **prompts**, **lyrics**, and **story**.  
- It ensures the visuals accurately reflect the lyrical meaning and narrative flow.  
- It provides a summary of what aligns and what may need adjustment.  
-  **Output:** A verification summary confirming lyrical and visual consistency.  

---

### 4 Final Step: Prompt Splitter Node
- After verification, copy the **final JSON** into the **Prompt Splitter Node**.

widgets_values:
##  WAN Models to Download

---

###  Main HUMO Model  
`Wan2_1-HuMo-14B_fp8_e4m3fn_scaled_KJ.safetensors'  
 [Download Link](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy_fp8_scaled/resolve/main/HuMo/Wan2_1-HuMo-14B_fp8_e4m3fn_scaled_KJ.safetensors?download=true)

---

### Whisper Model 
`Whisper Large`  
 [Download Link](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/resolve/main/HuMo/whisper_large_v3_encoder_fp16.safetensors)


---

###  WAN VAE  
`Wan2_1_VAE_bf16`  
 [Download Link](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/resolve/main/Wan2_1_VAE_bf16.safetensors?download=true)

OR

`wan2_1_vae_fp8`  
 [Download Link](https://huggingface.co/calcuis/wan-gguf/resolve/2a7520ea1e79d3f1f3f454a938613235633e1cba/wan2_1_vae_fp8.safetensors)

 Place in: `ComfyUI/models/vae`


---
###  WAN Text Encoder
`umt5-xxl-enc-bf16.safetensors`  
 [Download Link](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/resolve/main/umt5-xxl-enc-bf16.safetensors)

OR

`umt5-xxl-enc-fp8.safetensors`  
 [Download Link](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/resolve/main/umt5-xxl-enc-fp8_e4m3fn.safetensors)

---

 Place in: `ComfyUI/models/text_encoders`

---

###  Torch Compile Warning  
If your setup doesnt support torch compile, set attention mode to `sdpa` in the model loader, bypass the torch compile node and chang ethe base_precision to fp16

---

###  Block Swapping
Block swapping helps with Lower VRAM GPU's and OOM. You can swap up to 40 but it will decrease generation speed. Only use it if you need to. - Bypass if you do not need this
